def: One skilled in some trade or manual occupation; an artificer; amechanic.
The title of the ruling Prince of Baroda, in Gujarat, inBombay, India.
To paint or tinge with red lead or vermilion; also, to decoratewith letters, or the like, painted red, as the page of a manuscript.T. Wharton.
A cut; an incision; a gash. Derham.
A genus of rosaceous plants, including the raspberry andblackberry.
Of supreme chemical powers. [R.] "The archchemic sun." Milton.
To study or to talk astronomy. [R.]They astronomized in caves. Sir T. Browne.
The state of being a swordsman; skill in the use of the sword.Cowper.
The critical moment in a play, when, contrary to expectation,the action is embroiled in new difficulties. Dryden.
